Hell, I know I've heard George W. Bush refer to God in one of his speeches.  I guess that makes it unconstitutional since he's the President, but then again, is he not allowed to express his religious beliefs?  He has the same freedoms that everyone else has, right?<br>
<br>
If it bothers you that much, don't say it, organize protests, write your Congressman, whatever.  I just don't see what all the fuss is about.  If the Pledge being unconstitutional is killing babies or starving people or killing innocents, then by all means, change it.  If not, then why not turn your energies to something of more import.  I believe that people have the right to worship however they please, but I also believe there are more important things to worry about.<br>
<br>
