  I'm only about halfway through the discussion at this point, but I'm glad to see it here.  I won't bother with stating my view or giving reasons why, but I would like to mention...<br>
<br>
  Does this thread contain 200 posts in unanimous decision, either direction (200 being just a guess where it's at now)?  No, it certainly does not.  It's a discussion on both sides, yet our government doesn't appear to have a single politician who is willing to voice agreement with the decision.<br>
<br>
  Yes, I understand that it would be political suicide, but it still suprises me a bit that not a single person is willing to say something along the lines of, &quot;I understand the decision and think it is sound, but not viable or realistic in implementation in that it would blah and such and etc.&quot;<br>
<br>
  If those people are to be representing us, where is the discussion?  I guess I am simply expressing some level of suprise that the governing body does not represent the disparity of opinion on this subject in even the slightest degree.<br>
